<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html; charset=UTF-8"
    pageEncoding="UTF-8"%>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>KODAIKANAL</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.3/font/bootstrap-icons.min.css">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="places.css">
</head>
<body>
    <section id="destination" class="destination-places">
    </section>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="section-header text-center pb-3 mt-md-5">
                    <h1>PLACE TO VISIT</h1>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="des-container">
            <div class="ol-12 col-md-12 col-lg-4 pb-2">
                <div class="card overflow">
                    <img src="kodaikanal1.jpg" class="select">
                    <div class="intro">
                        <h1 class="placename">Kodaikanal Lake</h1>
                        <p class="aboutplace">Man-made, star-shaped lake, 60 acres, 3 km circumference, boating, fishing, walking path, scenic views, tranquil surroundings, picnic spot, sunset views.Surrounded by lush greenery, flowers. Boat house, cycling. Popular tourist destination.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ol-12 col-md-12 col-lg-4 pb-5">
                <div class="card overflow">
                    <img src="kodaikanal2.jpg" class="select">
                    <div class="intro">
                        <h1 class="placename">Pillar Rocks</h1>
                        <p class="aboutplace">Three giant rock formations, 122 meters tall, standing shoulder-to-shoulder. Unique geological wonder, formed by erosion. Surrounded by lush gardens, scenic views. Popular spot for photography, trekking. Located 7 km from Kodaikanal Lake.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ol-12 col-md-12 col-lg-4 pb-5">
                <div class="card overflow">
                    <img src="kodaikanal3.jpg" class="select">
                    <div class="intro">
                        <h1 class="placename">Coaker's Walk</h1>
                        <p class="aboutplace">Scenic 1-kilometer walking path along hill's edge. Offers breathtaking views of surrounding valleys, mountains, and Vaigai Dam. Named after Lt. Coaker, who discovered it in 1872. </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ol-12 col-md-12 col-lg-4 pb-5">
                <div class="card overflow">
                    <img src="kodaikanal4.jpg" class="select">
                    <div class="intro">
                        <h1 class="placename">Bryant Park</h1>
                        <p class="aboutplace">Bryant Park is located in Midtown Manhattan, New York City, between 40th and 42nd Streets and Fifth and Sixth Avenues.The park covers an area of 9.6 acres, making it a relatively small but popular green space in the heart of the city.</p></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ol-12 col-md-12 col-lg-4 pb-5">
                <div class="card overflow">
                    <img src="kodaikanal5.jpg" class="select">
                    <div class="intro">
                        <h1 class="placename">Guna Caves</h1>
                        <p class="aboutplace">The Guna Caves are a series of caves that stretch for over 1 kilometer, with some caves being as deep as 100 meters. The caves are home to a variety of unique rock formations, including stalactites and stalagmites, which are formed through the slow process of dripping water.</p>
                        </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ol-12 col-md-12 col-lg-4 pb-5">
                <div class="card overflow">
                    <img src="kodaikanal6.jpg" class="select">
                    <div class="intro">
                        <h1 class="placename">Silver Cascade</h1>
                        <p class="aboutplace">Silver Cascade is a beautiful waterfall located in the state of Tamil Nadu, India. It is a popular tourist destination and a must-visit spot for nature lovers and adventure seekers.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>